<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gore2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gore,</orth> vb. to stab, to pierce: <bibl n="shak. ven 616" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 616</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.115" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 115</bibl>. Metaphorically, to wound, to hurt deeply: <bibl n="shak. son 110.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 110, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 3.3.228" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. III, 3, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.320" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 320</bibl>.
